OL,6,GThe chairman of the BBC has been
OL,7,Gsetting out his thinking on
OL,8,Galternatives to the licence fee.
OL,10,FIn a wide-ranging interview in The
OL,11,FSunday Times, Samir Shah discusses
OL,12,Fpossible alternatives.
OL,14,FHis comments on radical changes will
OL,15,Fbe familiar to all who have followed
OL,16,Fthis debate, recently and in the past.
OL,18,FAdvertising would "violate the core
OL,19,Fprinciple that the BBC is independent
OL,20,Fof commercial interests ` and kill
OL,21,FITV".
