OL,6,FA subscription service "would not meet
OL,7,Fthe BBC's key role to offer something
OL,8,Ffor everyone in the country".
OL,10,FFunding from general taxation would
OL,11,F"leave the BBC open to influence from
OL,12,Fthe government of the day".
OL,14,FHe also dismisses the idea of a hybrid
OL,15,Fmodel with different tiers of service
OL,16,F` such as a licence fee to pay for the
OL,17,Fbasic service with subscriptions for
OL,18,Fpremium content.
