OL,3,CBBC chairman discusses licence fee
OL,4,Calternatives
OL,6,FIt is generally accepted within the
OL,7,Findustry that if the BBC were ever to
OL,8,Fcarry advertising, the size of the
OL,9,Fadvertising market would not grow ` it
OL,10,Fwould simply mean that others would
OL,11,Fget less, possibly threatening their
OL,12,Fviability.
OL,14,FThe result of the General Election
OL,15,Fchanged the terms of reference for the
OL,16,Fdebate on the BBC's future.
OL,18,FThere is no longer an immediate
OL,19,Fexistential threat. Those who would
OL,20,F"defund the BBC" or seek radical
OL,21,Fchange no longer have the ear of
OL,22,Fanyone in the Cabinet.
